(firstQuint)Randomized Controlled Trials on Laparoscopic No.

 14v LNS Dissection.

 A prospective randomized comparison of laparoscopic No.

 14v lymph node dissection in advanced lower third gastric cancer will be performed, to evaluate the short-term, long-term and oncological outcomes.

 The evaluation parameters are perioperative clinical efficacy, postoperative life quality, immune function and 3-year survival and recurrence rates.

